    "field_name": "Immunology",
    "field_description": "\nIn principle, the immune system surveys essentially the entire body and stores a memory of much of what it finds. The system is theoretically highly programmable by inserting or removing DNA-encoded adaptive immune receptor molecules. However, our current ability to read-write this system is limited and new tools and datasets are needed to harness its power. While [data suggest](https://www.nature.com/articles/35008096) that antigens displayed on the cell surface may not be well predicted by DNA sequences and genetic code, the ability to unbiasedly identify and _de novo_ sequence antigens remains limited. \n\n",
